We have recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to direct the officials to device internal control and monitoring mechanisms to ensure that all grants and donations made to barangays are properly documented and utilized for public purpose, which includes but not limited to the following:

Demand a copy of Sangguniang Barangay Resolution for acceptance of donations granted to barangays, attach the same to the Disbursement Vouchers as part of documentation; afterwards, the Municipal Accountant shall record in the books of the Barangays items donated to them; 

For requests of rice/ grocery items and other supplies for distribution, demand the barangays to prepare list of households or beneficiaries to justify the quantity of items to be procured. After distribution, require the barangays to present acknowledgement receipts, photos, signed lists, or any other form of documentations proving that these were received and fully distributed;

Demand the recipient barangays to put inventory tags on monobloc tables and chairs, other similar semi-expendable properties, and PPEs donated to them; and duly record these items in their books of accounts; and

to instruct the management to strictly adhere with Section 122 of MNGAS for LGUs on requisition and subsequent issuance of supplies and inventories. The purchased supplies/ inventories for donation to barangays must be first inspected by the GSO before distribution to the recipients.

