We have recommended the management the following:
for the management to issue demand letters and apply legal sanctions as needed especially for due and demandable receivables from disallowances;
to formulate collection scheme in order to enforce collection in order to decrease and gradually eradicate the uncollectible balance;
to identify and pursue the retired accountable officers who absconded from their responsibility, and to seek legal remedies against the estate of the deceased accountable officers to compensate for the monetary value of the lost accountable forms.

We have further recommended the management to devise and implement strict internal control mechanism in handling accountable forms to prevent any more losses.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct all concerned officials and employees to settle immediately their unliquidated cash advances. Failure to do so would warrant the filing of malversation case against the erring officials/employees under Article 217;
Require the withholding of salaries and other emoluments in full of officials and employees who are still in service effective immediately and apply the said withheld amounts in their respective outstanding cash advances;
Require the former Vice Mayor to sign authorization letter to deduct the outstanding cash advances from his terminal pay;
Enjoin all concerned officials and employees to strictly comply with rules/regulations on the proper granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances per COA Circular No. 97-002 and Section 82 of PD 1445; and
In the case of the unliquidated cash advance of the deceased accountable officers, legal advice should be sought on how the LGU could impose the settlement of the cash advance through their heirs. In case that this remedy is futile, then those who approved and released any benefits due him, without considering the deduction of the subject cash advance, should be held liable.

We have recommended the management the following:
For the Local Chief Executive to create an investigation committee to conduct an investigation on the identity of the erring official and, if proven beyond reasonable doubt, take legal actions as needed;
For the Sangguniang Bayan to refer to the Local Chief Executive, and in coordination with the Municipal Social Welfare and Development Office (MSWDO), the qualification of the persons requesting for assistance/donations to ensure that these are only granted to eligible constituents;
In the case of the Requests of Barangay Officials, all monetary assistances must be receipted thru issuance of Accountable Form No. 51 by the Barangay and subsequently be deposited in their respective Barangay Accounts. These must be recorded in their Registry of Estimated and Actual Income (REAI). As for the construction materials and inventories, these must be received with Sangguniang Barangay Resolution authorizing the barangay to receive the donations, copies of which will form part of the supporting documents of disbursement vouchers to be prepared by the LGU; and
For the Municipal Accountant to recognize in the books of the Barangays all donations recorded as given by the LGU.

