The Municipal Treasurer to deposit all collections daily and intact pursuant to the provisions of Section 69 of PD 1445 and Section 32 of Manual on New Government Accounting System Volume I, and regularly update her cashbooks to reflect the exact amount of collections and deposits;
For the Liquidating Officer to transmit to the Municipal Treasurer the report of remittances made by the Collecting Officers daily;
To enjoin all Accountable Officers to strictly prohibit the encashment of checks from the collections; and
For the Municipal Treasurer, thru the Local Chief Executive, to write a memorandum to the business establishments to issue two checks which bear half of the amount of their Real Property Tax payment for each check. This will facilitate the recording of RPT collections and deposits of the Treasury Unit for General Fund and Special Education Fund.

Direct all concerned officials and employees to settle immediately their unliquidated cash advances or best, demand letter should be issued. The failure of those concerned to liquidate their respective cash advances would mean that liquidation or refund would be demanded from the officials/employees responsible in allowing /approving cash advances, particularly on those with cash advances approved despite the none liquidation of previous cash advances;
Require the withholding of salaries and other emoluments in full of officials and employees who are still in service effective immediately and apply the said withheld amounts in their respective unliquidated outstanding cash advances;
Instruct the Municipal Accountant and other department heads to strictly comply with rules/regulations on the proper granting, utilization and liquidation of cash advances per COA Circular No. 97-002 and Section 82 of PD 1445; and
In the case of the unliquidated cash advance of the deceased accountable officers, legal advice should be sought on how the LGU could impose the settlement of the cash advance through their heirs. In case that this remedy is futile, then those who approved and released any benefits due him, without considering the deduction of the subject cash advance, should be held liable.

For the Municipal Treasurer to prepare Real Property Tax Account Register/Taxpayer’s index card and compare her records with the Municipal Assessor, and subsequently prepare the certified list of taxpayers showing the amount due and collectible, and afterwards submit the list to the Municipal Accountant for the set-up of RPT and SET receivables at the beginning of the year;
For the Municipal Assessor to coordinate and reconcile her records with the Municipal Treasurer to facilitate the preparation of the certified list of taxpayers; and
Subsequently, a report on RPT delinquencies must be prepared by the Treasury unit and impose penalties and avail remedies set by laws to compel the delinquent taxpayers to pay their taxes on time.

Enjoin the agency drivers to accomplish driver’s rip tickets, monthly summarized report of travels, and monthly report of fuel consumption;
For the Municipal Accountant to check the completeness of supporting documents before certifying the disbursement vouchers;
For the officials receiving travel allowance to refrain from reimbursing gasoline/diesel and oil expenses for travels within 50-km radius from the official station;
To ensure that no government vehicle is to be used for purposes other than official business; and
To refrain from reimbursing gasoline/diesel, and oil when a private vehicle is used notwithstanding whether the purpose of travel is for official business.

Require the consultants to submit curriculum vitae and other relevant information that would support their credentials and eligibilities in their chosen field of expertise and for the management to create a databank of the consultants’ credentials/qualifications in order to determine whether their accomplishments are conformable to their qualifications and to justify their appointment as consultants;
Stop the practice of hiring consultants for tasks which do not require expertise and that can be performed by the regular employees to avoid incurrence of additional expenditure which unfavourable to the agency;
Specify in the contract the duties and responsibilities to be performed by the Consultants, and compare those against their actual outputs/ accomplishments to ascertain whether or not they are able to deliver their functions expected, otherwise the hiring is unjustified; and
Require the acquiescence / approval from the Office of the Solicitor General (OSG) and COA in hiring legal consultants. Non-conformity to these requirements would mean disallowance of the remunerations paid to them.
